<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9567] Windows does not handle ipv6 addresses</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9567</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In cassandra.ps1, we are pulling the listen and rpc addresses from the yaml by splitting on &lt;tt&gt;:&lt;/tt&gt;, then selecting &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; from the resulting split, to separate the yaml key from the value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, because ipv6 addresses contain &lt;tt&gt;:&lt;/tt&gt; characters, this means we are not grabbing the whole address, causing problems when starting the node.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
